text: Frederick of Brunswick-Lüneburg may refer to: * Frederick I, Duke of Brunswick-Lüneburg (c.1357–1400) * Frederick II, Duke of Brunswick-Lüneburg (1418–1478), also called Frederick the Pious * Frederick III, Duke of Brunswick-Lüneburg (1424-1495), also called Frederick the Restless * Frederick IV, Duke of Brunswick-Lüneburg (1574–1648) * Frederick Ulrich, Duke of Brunswick-Wolfenbüttel (1591–1634) * Frederick Charles Ferdinand, Duke of Brunswick-Lüneburg (1729–1809) * Frederick William, Duke of Brunswick- Wolfenbüttel (1771–1815)
title: Frederick of Brunswick-Lüneburg
